  "excerpt": "As a contributor for Studio Calico , I only receive kits on occasion now. It was really freeing only having to do 1 small assignment, but at the same time I miss the joy in in having to document my…",
  "legacyPath": "/blog/2015/1/26/studio-calico-cirque-contributor",
  "legacyFile": "blog__2015__1__26__studio-calico-cirque-contributor.html",
  "imageCount": 5,
  "body": "<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/cf2c63a2d510b586.jpg?v=1782537983\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>As a contributor for Studio Calico, I only receive kits on occasion now. It was really freeing only having to do 1 small assignment, but at the same time I miss the joy in in having to document my memories with all the fun products on a monthly basis. And I missed the need to make a mess on my desk. I used the Project Life kit and Pantomime for this one pager. I'm still working on filling in some (okay maybe a lot of) blanks for my 2014 album.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/d76f579de458e7eb.jpg?v=1782537985\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Decided I would have to have at least 1 spread or page that represents each month in the 2014 album. This will make it easier to fill in the blanks (I think). I definitely wanted to include the days we spent in Florida, even though it wasn't a complete week, and it went from a Friday to Wednesday in November. Since this page made sense to go chronologically after the Hello Kitty event, I had to use the back of this page. For the square pockets, I intended on keeping it pretty simple. Instead of leaving the grey cardstock from my stash plain, I cut the card into strips and adhered it to fill in the sides next to the photo. With the other 2 cards, I added the washi tape on the sides. I love the way they turned out. The sunshine is from the adorable Spring Card + Sticker Set by Life.Love.Paper. - and the best part is that it's just $5.99. The script \"Time for new things\" card is part of that set too!</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/c4f00c33fbe8b633.jpg?v=1782537988\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/b47463cf5a03cb2f.jpg?v=1782537991\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0981/5667/5392/files/2740c73c75cfcde9.jpg?v=1782537994\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>So there you have it, a couple more pages to add to the 2014 album. How are you all doing on your memory keeping from last year? I think I am going to just fill in the blanks that I can and not stress about the rest. There's plenty of new memories to be made! Plus, if I feel it's important at a later time, I can always go back and do it. Who's with me?!</p><p>You can shop for all Cirque kits here and see my projects here.</p><p><em>Keep in mind that </em><em>subscribers</em><em> can shop the pre-sale each month at noon EST on the 27th. Others need to wait until the clock strikes midnight tonight. </em><em>Become a subscriber</em><em> and get in on all the benefits and rewards that </em><em>Studio Calico</em><em> has to offer!</em></p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
